observations.recommendation:
We recommended that: The City Mayor direct the conduct of proper investigation on all Accountable Officers at the City Treasurer’s to determine all persons responsible and liable on the irregularities that occurred therein, submit a report thereon and file appropriate charges, if necessary, as soon as possible;

The City Treasurer install a strong internal control measures to ensure that issuance of Official Receipt could not be altered by any Accountable Officer and the access to the computerized system must be assigned only to authorized employees of the Office and monitor activities of collectors to ensure that they are adhering to existing rules and regulations; and

Moreover, she must not allow the collection function to employees who are not duly designated as collectors and not properly bonded pursuant to Section 101 of PD 1445 and Sec. 305(f) RA No. 7160.

We recommended and management agreed to:
Ensure that the Fidelity bond of Accountable Officer is increased to an amount sufficient to cover their maximum cash accountabilities to protect the interest of the City in case of loss from the unlawful use of government funds and those attributable to negligence in the safekeeping of such funds;
Otherwise, assign another accountable officer to draw the excess   cash advances over the maximum cash accountability of one accountable to another officer with higher approved amount of bond.

The City Mayor demand immediate settlement/liquidation of unliquidated cash advances pursuant to Item 6.0 of COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated November 28, 2012 for those granted before December 31, 2011;

The City Accountant require the accountable officers to strictly comply with the guidelines provided in Items 5.8 of COA Circular No. 97-002 and Section 89 of P.D. 1445 in the liquidation of their cash advances; and

She must monitor the liquidation and demand settlement if no liquidation was submitted within the prescribed period.
